{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Similarly, Marvin Minsky, a leading pioneer in AI, predicted in 1967 that the challenge of creating AI would be substantially solved within a generation [21].",
    "Although there were some noteworthy achievements in the early days, such as General Problem Solver, checkers, and the invention of the AI programming language LISP [2], by the late 1960s and early 1970s, researchers faced considerable hurdles in advancing the technology.",
    "It became apparent that the AI systems of the time struggled to address realworld problems effectively.",
    "As a result, securing funding for AI projects became increasingly difficult, leading to the first AI winter.",
    "A brief resurgence of AI enthusiasm emerged in the late 1970s and early 1980s, spurred by the proliferation of rule-based expert systems [22]."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
